com.azure.messaging.eventhubs

Class PartitionProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.azure.messaging.eventhubs.PartitionProcessor

  • public abstract class PartitionProcessor
extends Object
    An abstract class defining all the operations that a partition processor can perform. Users of EventProcessor should extend from this class and implement PartitionProcessor.processEvent(PartitionContext, EventData) for processing events. Additionally, users can override:
    • PartitionProcessor.initialize(PartitionContext) - This method is called before at the beginning of processing a partition.
    • PartitionProcessor.processError(PartitionContext, Throwable) - This method is called if there is an error while processing events
    • PartitionProcessor.close(PartitionContext, CloseReason) - This method is called at the end of processing a partition. The CloseReason specifies why the processing of a partition stopped.

    An instance of partition processor will process events from a single partition only.

    Implementations of this abstract class also have the responsibility of updating checkpoints when appropriate.

        public abstract Mono<Void> processEvent(PartitionContext partitionContext,

      • processError

        public void processError(PartitionContext partitionContext,
                         Throwable throwable)
        This method is called when an error occurs while receiving events from Event Hub. An error also marks the end of event data stream.
        Parameters:
        partitionContext - The partition information where the error occurred.
        throwable - The Throwable that caused this method to be called.

      • close

        public Mono<Void> close(PartitionContext partitionContext,
                        CloseReason closeReason)
        This method is called before the partition processor is closed. A partition processor could be closed for various reasons and the reasons and implementations of this interface can take appropriate actions to cleanup before the partition processor is shutdown.
        Parameters:
        partitionContext - The partition information for which the processing of events is closed.
        closeReason - The reason for closing this partition processor.
        Returns:
        a representation of the deferred computation of this call.
